entry.title: Russia reacts with glee to Trump-Zelensky exchange

media:group.media:title: Russia reacts with glee to Trump-Zelensky exchange
media:group.media:description: Russian officials reacted with glee to the furious Trump-Zelensky exchange in the Oval Office. The Kremlin hopes that the impact could go well beyond the war in Ukraine – even completely redrawing the US-Russia relationship, CNN's Matthew Chance reports from Moscow. #cnn #news #russia #trump #politics

entry.title: Hear Democratic senator’s advice for Zelensky

media:group.media:title: Hear Democratic senator’s advice for Zelensky
media:group.media:description: Senator Chris Van Hollen criticized President Donald Trump and Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky's contentious Oval Office meeting, calling it “reprehensible.” The Maryland Democrat explained why he believes Trump sees himself as a strongman like Russian President Vladimir Putin or Chinese leader Xi Jinping. #CNN #News

entry.title: This former teacher is living our retirement dreams in France

media:group.media:title: This former teacher is living our retirement dreams in France
media:group.media:description: Janice Deerwester moved to France at 70 and has been chronicling the ups and downs of her new life on her YouTube channel, ‘Janice in France.’ She’s found an incredible community and says she has yet to meet one rude person. #CNN #livingabroad #shorts @JaniceInFrance

entry.title: ‘That is just asking for disaster to happen,’ warns fired NOAA worker

media:group.media:title: ‘That is just asking for disaster to happen,’ warns fired NOAA worker
media:group.media:description: Cuts to the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) will result in mistakes being made, a recently laid-off staffer told CNN. Speaking to CNN, Tom Di Liberto said the organization was already short-staffed, and understaffing as an issue will now only be exacerbated. #CNN #News
